00:41:13.250 --> 00:41:15.540
Scott to pee in a cup.

00:41:15.540 --> 00:41:17.300
We were doing a
piece down in Florida

00:41:17.300 --> 00:41:21.770
about mandatory drug testing
for people on welfare.

00:41:27.325 --> 00:41:28.200
It was a valid piece.

00:41:28.200 --> 00:41:30.520
But what was great
about it was, Rick Scott

00:41:30.520 --> 00:41:33.690
was having a press conference
to announce his budget

00:41:33.690 --> 00:41:34.710
for the upcoming year.

00:41:34.710 --> 00:41:35.590
And we thought it
would be great.

00:41:35.590 --> 00:41:38.256
Because what we realized is that
like, a lot of these people who

00:41:38.256 --> 00:41:41.740
are advocating this
law, their reasoning

00:41:41.740 --> 00:41:43.199
was that welfare
is taxpayer money.

00:41:43.199 --> 00:41:44.615
And therefore, the
taxpayer should

00:41:44.615 --> 00:41:46.030
know where that money is going.

00:41:46.030 --> 00:41:47.910
And so these people
should be drug tested.

00:41:47.910 --> 00:41:49.490
But surprise, surprise.

00:41:49.490 --> 00:41:51.650
The people who
are also lawmakers

00:41:51.650 --> 00:41:54.310
in the state of Florida are
getting paid by the taxpayer.

00:41:54.310 --> 00:41:57.155
And so why should they not
be drug tested, as well?

00:41:57.155 --> 00:41:59.030
So this was our premise
that we went in with,

00:41:59.030 --> 00:42:01.150
and we thought we would
take it to the highest

00:42:01.150 --> 00:42:04.270
level in Florida, which
is the governor himself.

00:42:04.270 --> 00:42:07.175
And so we interrupted a
press conference of his

00:42:07.175 --> 00:42:08.800
with about as many
journalists as there

00:42:08.800 --> 00:42:11.050
are sitting in this
room right now,

00:42:11.050 --> 00:42:15.500
and asked him if he would
give us a urine sample.

00:42:15.500 --> 00:42:16.750
And I had the cup right there.

00:42:16.750 --> 00:42:17.610
I said, you can do it right now.

00:42:17.610 --> 00:42:18.950
We'll all turn around.

00:42:18.950 --> 00:42:21.930
You could just give
us a quick sample.

00:42:21.930 --> 00:42:23.732
And he was not happy about that.

00:42:26.480 --> 00:42:29.060
I think at first, he
was trying to be polite.

00:42:29.060 --> 00:42:31.420
But eventually, he
was like, I'm running

00:42:31.420 --> 00:42:33.090
this press conference,
not you, OK?

00:42:33.090 --> 00:42:33.630
Sit down.

00:42:33.630 --> 00:42:36.290
And so even though he
got mad and shut us up,

00:42:36.290 --> 00:42:37.980
we had the moment.

00:42:37.980 --> 00:42:41.280
And what was great about it was,
when it aired-- first of all,

00:42:41.280 --> 00:42:45.950
before it aired-- because
every media outlet in Florida

00:42:45.950 --> 00:42:47.230
was in that room.

00:42:47.230 --> 00:42:52.020
Meanwhile, none of them made a
sound while I was doing this.

00:42:52.020 --> 00:42:55.120
They were just
gobsmacked and sat there,

00:42:55.120 --> 00:42:58.020
afraid to laugh,
afraid to do anything.

00:42:58.020 --> 00:42:59.880
Because they want to
get in that room again,

00:42:59.880 --> 00:43:01.020
and I don't give a shit.

00:43:01.020 --> 00:43:01.990
You know what I mean?

00:43:01.990 --> 00:43:06.920
So they're all like, we want to
be invited to this party again.

00:43:06.920 --> 00:43:09.350
We are not going to
make fun of the host.

00:43:09.350 --> 00:43:10.620
So they all sat there.

00:43:10.620 --> 00:43:14.980
But the minute we walked
out, they came upon us.

00:43:14.980 --> 00:43:17.390
And they were literally
like, that was amazing.

00:43:17.390 --> 00:43:20.110
We wish we could do that.

00:43:20.110 --> 00:43:24.000
And then it was in all
the Florida newspapers,

00:43:24.000 --> 00:43:25.950
it was on all the local news.

00:43:25.950 --> 00:43:28.550
And my parents, who live
in Tampa, of course,

00:43:28.550 --> 00:43:30.770
my dad calls me.

00:43:30.770 --> 00:43:32.220
And he just answered the phone.

00:43:32.220 --> 00:43:32.845
I'm like, what?

00:43:32.845 --> 00:43:34.130
He's like, what did you do?

00:43:38.770 --> 00:43:42.050
And he had heard it on the
radio and on the local news.

00:43:42.050 --> 00:43:45.280
And then when the piece aired,
I realized how much Floridians

00:43:45.280 --> 00:43:50.050
hate Rick Scott, and they
were so happy that happened.

00:43:50.050 --> 00:43:53.570
So that's one of my
personal favorites as well.

