00:52:05.260 --> 00:52:06.676
AUDIENCE: (TRINI
ACCENT) You can't

00:52:06.676 --> 00:52:09.790
do a Trini accent like me.

00:52:09.790 --> 00:52:11.535
AASIF MANDVI: Nice, nice.

00:52:11.535 --> 00:52:13.160
AUDIENCE: And I also
moved around a lot

00:52:13.160 --> 00:52:14.290
once I moved to America.

00:52:14.290 --> 00:52:17.270
So I was wondering,
did you ever reconcile

00:52:17.270 --> 00:52:19.870
all of those different
pieces and parts of yourself

00:52:19.870 --> 00:52:21.090
into one single identity?

00:52:21.090 --> 00:52:23.720
Or do you still think
of it as, well, there

00:52:23.720 --> 00:52:25.530
are just multiple
parts to my identity.

00:52:25.530 --> 00:52:29.620
AASIF MANDVI: I think
the multiplicity becomes

00:52:29.620 --> 00:52:32.494
the source of where your
creativity comes from,

00:52:32.494 --> 00:52:34.660
where your power comes from,
where all of that stuff

00:52:34.660 --> 00:52:36.770
comes from.

00:52:36.770 --> 00:52:40.010
I'm jealous of people
who are one thing

00:52:40.010 --> 00:52:44.930
and can identify with
that one thing as them.

00:52:44.930 --> 00:52:46.000
I've never felt that.

00:52:46.000 --> 00:52:48.500
So the multiplicity
and the shapeshifting

00:52:48.500 --> 00:52:53.070
has always been my source
of power and creativity.

00:52:53.070 --> 00:52:57.140
So it took me a
long time to realize

00:52:57.140 --> 00:52:59.250
that was a positive,
and not a negative.

00:52:59.250 --> 00:53:07.900
But once I got there, I realize
that now, that is what I do.

00:53:07.900 --> 00:53:09.111
Good question, good question.

